    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">basically, you put out sam right away (after bidding 5-7 to make sure you go first), remove burdens, then drop allies and draw cards until you&#39;re sure you&#39;re safe with enough swan ships/homely houses to defend yourself.  try to always move two times, unless you&#39;re facing multiple fierce uruk-hai.<br />
<br />
try and keep your companions alive, obviously, but since there are really no &#39;component&#39; cards for any of them, it&#39;s not so bad if they do.  after all they&#39;re just frodo&#39;s shield.  <br />
<br />
never put out aragorn (unless you really need him) until you&#39;re at site 6, and about to move to 7.  also, if you&#39;re holding extra copies of allies which are already in play, keep them in your hand in case you hit the anti-allies site 7.<br />
<br />
don&#39;t use aragorn&#39;s defender +3 ability until you walk into site 9 and get swamped (unless it&#39;s absolutely necessary).<br />
<br />
it&#39;s a sure win when you have aragorn, 3 other companions and frodo, and your opponent can only put out 5 minions.  you auto-win.<br />
